Brett Lightbody, Jun 28, 2024, 14:19 GMT+1

Hi Ben,

I believe the best way to resolve this would be for your IT to update the SSL certificate manually on the InVentry system with my below instructions.


1. _**On the sign in screen, triple click on the InVentry Logo on your home screen - this is usually in the bottom left of the screen**_
2. _**When the keypad appears enter the first 4 digits of your Anywhere ID (0632) or 1234**_
3. _**From the options that appear please select 'Shutdown InVentry', you will then see a normal PC desktop**_
4. _**An orange box will appear in the bottom right corner, please tap this then press 'Ok' in the window that appears in the centre of the screen (if you miss this the sign in screen will reload and you will need to complete the first 3 steps again.**_
5. _**Log off the InVentry_system user**_
6. _**Log onto the local admin user "Inventry" with the password "Inventry1983" (capital "i")**_
7. _**Run through steps 1-4 again to close down the software**_

Cut the "Silent Installer" folder to the below location.

C:\Program Files\Inventry\V4

Cut the 2 certificate files to the below location.

C:\Program Files\Inventry\V4\Service

Once the files are in the correct folders, go back into the "Silent Installer" and right click "Run as administrator" on the "Silent Installer.exe"

This should then present a CMD prompt and confirm the results of the SSL certificate update.

You can also confirm this by opening a new CMD window and entering the below command.

Netsh HTTP show sslcert

Please note you will have to extract the .RAR files.

Kind regards,
Brett.

[image: Wonde] <https://wonde.com>

Hi Kirsten,

We’re contacting you because *Vale of York Academy* is currently sharing
daily attendance data with the *Department for Education (DfE).*

The DfE are updating some of the data fields that you share with them.
Sharing this data will mean you are sharing all required fields to meet the
DfE’s new statutory requirement regarding submission of school attendance
data, effective from 18 August 2024.

*Data fields*

DfE are asking that you update and approve the following data fields within
your Wonde portal:


   - SEN rank content read
   - SEN type code content read
   - Special education needs read
   - Students address read
   - Students contact details read
   - Students first language read
   - Students legal forename read
   - Students middle names read
   - Students legal surname read




   - Students leaver first language read
   - Students leaver legal forename read
   - Students leaver legal surname read
   - Students leaver middle names read
   - Students leaver contact details read
   - Students leaver address read



*Next steps *

   1. Go to your *Wonde portal* <https://edu.wonde.com/login> and select
   the *DfE* tile
   2. Review the updated fields in the permissions section
   3. Approve the request, if you're happy to do so

If you have any questions, please contact the *Wonde* Support Team for
further information.

Kind regards

respond and confirm a date when access can be arranged.
*Here are our top tips to avoid common Cashless pitfalls:*
*1. Act now!* Almost all problems are avoidable with a bit of planning and
we’re here to help. Don’t risk a disrupted lunch service when schools
return.

*2. Check if any IT changes are planned *and *tell us before Friday 28 June
2024 *so that we can book in any work that needs to be completed. IT
changes are the biggest source of problems at the start of a new term.
Disruptors include:

   - A change of MIS provider
   - A change of ePayment provider
   - Switch, Firewall, Network Config, Wireless and Smoothwall changes
   - IP address changes
   - Server migrations
   - TRUSTe license installations.

*3. Make Free School Meal changes as soon as schools break up.* Pushing out
price changes then means you’ll iron out issues early and be ready when
schools return. We can provide guidance on this if required.

*4. Get help with menu updates.* If you’re planning a full menu update,
then we can do this for you, providing additional peace of mind. Simply
tell us *before Friday 28 June* *2024 *so that we can provide a quote and
book this in.

*5. Check you have access to the school calendar in TRUSTe*. If not, please
get in touch ASAP so we can add this for you. It’s important to update your
School Holidays and ensure the system is on the correct date ready for the
new term.

*6. Check your Free Meal Allocation is correct.* This is either updated in
Account Types in TRUSTe or centrally by your council or catering group. If
you use ParentPay, ensure the school office has updated the allowance with
ParentPay too.

*7. Add your pre-admissions to the system.* This way you can capture
fingerprints on an induction day before their first day of school. Students
will first need to be entered into the school’s management information
system to show in Civica Cashless Catering.

*8. Power on your tills before you need them!* Make sure they are
operational and on the correct date. This can be done on any cleaning days
before students return.

*9. Take a copy of the backup* and store it away from the cashless server
to guard against ransomeware attacks.

Hi,
 Carl had just asked for me to document a bit of the use of The J drive. I
think the problem we have is that this share is a historical share that was
set up for staff to share files with students. It is a read only drive so
students can only view and download documents. They can't append them. I
think because it is historical, some staff are unaware of its purpose and
have been using it as a "staff share", instead of a "student share". Not
realising that students can read and download whatever they put in there.
Staff should use K drive for such things.

The only time that students can view these files is when they are logged
onto a school PC, it isn't available on ipads or chromebooks. So, is
only really available now in computer science and DT when they are using
the laptops and possibly in music.

*Recommendations:*

   - I would recommend that the read only access for students is removed
   from J drive at least in the short term. I very rarely use it, Dave Lowe
   says they never use it and so I'm sure Dave Allen doesn't. All the stuff I
   want to share with the students can be done through google classroom. So, I
   feel it is redundant. Unless there is a use for it elsewhere. This would
   limit the chance of inappropriate data being read or shared by students.
   - I would also recommend staff in all departments do an audit on the
   contents there (and possibly K Drive), as there are historical photos of
   students and staff as well as documents that may break GDPR rules: that
   only relevant data should be stored for only as long as it is necessary and
   that permission has been given by the subjects to hold this data and that
   it only shared with people who need this data.

Sorry for the long email, but in my previous role this was taken very
seriously in case a subject access request was put in. If students can see
data and there is a possibility that they find data about siblings or
uncles and Aunts (some of the data goes back to 2012) and word gets out, we
could end up in trouble.
Thank you,
Tim.

>>
>>
>> Debbie, as one of the UK’s leading cashless catering providers, we know
>> that calls to our helpdesk will always peak when children head back to
>> school in late August and early September.
>> Between the end of summer term and the start of the autumn term our
>> Cashless support team will be looking to dial into as many schools as
>> possible to perform health checks for the new term.  When contacted please
>> respond and confirm a date when access can be arranged.
>> *Here are our top tips to avoid common Cashless pitfalls:*
>> *1. Act now!* Almost all problems are avoidable with a bit of planning
>> and we’re here to help. Don’t risk a disrupted lunch service when schools
>> return.
>>
>> *2. Check if any IT changes are planned *and *tell us before Friday 28
>> June 2024 *so that we can book in any work that needs to be completed.
>> IT changes are the biggest source of problems at the start of a new term.
>> Disruptors include:
>>
>>    - A change of MIS provider
>>    - A change of ePayment provider
>>    - Switch, Firewall, Network Config, Wireless and Smoothwall changes
>>    - IP address changes
>>    - Server migrations
>>    - TRUSTe license installations.
>>
>> *3. Make Free School Meal changes as soon as schools break up.* Pushing
>> out price changes then means you’ll iron out issues early and be ready when
>> schools return. We can provide guidance on this if required.
>>
>> *4. Get help with menu updates.* If you’re planning a full menu update,
>> then we can do this for you, providing additional peace of mind. Simply
>> tell us *before Friday 28 June* *2024 *so that we can provide a quote
>> and book this in.
>>
>> *5. Check you have access to the school calendar in TRUSTe*. If not,
>> please get in touch ASAP so we can add this for you. It’s important to
>> update your School Holidays and ensure the system is on the correct date
>> ready for the new term.
>>
>> *6. Check your Free Meal Allocation is correct.* This is either updated
>> in Account Types in TRUSTe or centrally by your council or catering group.
>> If you use ParentPay, ensure the school office has updated the allowance
>> with ParentPay too.
>>
>> *7. Add your pre-admissions to the system.* This way you can capture
>> fingerprints on an induction day before their first day of school. Students
>> will first need to be entered into the school’s management information
>> system to show in Civica Cashless Catering.
>>
>> *8. Power on your tills before you need them!* Make sure they are
>> operational and on the correct date. This can be done on any cleaning days
>> before students return.
>>
>> *9. Take a copy of the backup* and store it away from the cashless
>> server to guard against ransomeware attacks.
>> *Get in touch*
>> <https://app.hello.civica.co.uk/e/er?s=3121&lid=14097&elqTrackId=D270977988511F00C166C0A54188DEC9&elq=7bd2c62b125b4162aa243b18cb6a3ac8&elqaid=12702&elqat=1>

5. _**If you can then double tap the TeamViewer icon  on the desktop**_
6. _**This should then open the TeamViewer application and provide you with an ID and a password. If you can please send these to us and leave the TeamViewer software open.**_
7. _**To reload the sign in software double tap the 'InVentry Core' icon on the desktop**_

Kind regards,
Brett.

We will be waiting for your response.

Kind regards,

Sachin Gupta

Hi Matt,

Thank you for your time.

I tried to remote onto your unit, but as per the error message received, it seems like either the unit is offline or the TeamViewer credentials that we have for your site are outdated. So, if you could please make sure that the unit is online and provide us with the updated TeamViewer credentials:




1. _**On the sign in screen, triple click on the InVentry Logo on your home screen - this is usually in the bottom left of the screen**_
2. _**When the keypad appears enter your PIN: "1234" or "0632".**_
3. _**From the options that appear please select 'Shutdown InVentry', you will then see a normal PC desktop**_
4. _**An orange box will appear in the bottom right corner, please tap this then press 'Ok' in the window that appears in the centre of the screen (if you miss this the sign in screen will reload and you will need to complete the first 3 steps again)**_
5. _**If you can then double tap the TeamViewer icon  on the desktop**_
6. _**This should then open the TeamViewer application and provide you with an ID and a password. If you can please send these to us and leave the TeamViewer software open.**_
7. _**To reload the sign in software double tap the 'InVentry Core' icon on the desktop**_

We will be waiting for your response.

Kind regards,

Sachin Gupta

Amit Waghole, Jun 18, 2024, 11:34 GMT+1

Hello Stephen,

Thank you for your query regarding upgrading Windows on your InVentry system from Windows 7 to Windows 10.

We at InVentry are unable to upgrade the Windows version for you as we do not hold license keys to conduct this process. The InVentry system however is the schools property and you are able to use the schools Windows license key to complete the upgrade.

We must stress the importance that the upgrade process is conducted manually as the use of an image will remove all InVentry software (including the database) from the system. We are unable to image the systems remotely so unfortunately our only option, should this happen, is to arrange for a new hard drive to be fitted and this will incur a fee for the site visit.

Online Instructions on how to complete this process including a checklist of key points are available on our support portal via the link below :

https://inventry.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/360004824977

I have provided the Windows administrator credentials verbally via telephone.

Once you have completed the upgrade of the Windows client you will then need to contact the InVentry Support team so that we can ensure the system is running correctly.

If you do have any further queries regarding this please let us know.

Kind regards

Amit Waghole

Sachin Gupta, Jun 12, 2024, 18:34 GMT+1

Hi Matt,

Thank you for your time.

I tried to remote onto your unit, but as per the error message received, it seems like either the unit is offline or the TeamViewer credentials that we have for your site are outdated. So, if you could please make sure that the unit is online and provide us with the updated TeamViewer credentials:




1. _**On the sign in screen, triple click on the InVentry Logo on your home screen - this is usually in the bottom left of the screen**_
2. _**When the keypad appears enter your PIN: "1234" or "0632".**_
3. _**From the options that appear please select 'Shutdown InVentry', you will then see a normal PC desktop**_
4. _**An orange box will appear in the bottom right corner, please tap this then press 'Ok' in the window that appears in the centre of the screen (if you miss this the sign in screen will reload and you will need to complete the first 3 steps again)**_
5. _**If you can then double tap the TeamViewer icon  on the desktop**_
6. _**This should then open the TeamViewer application and provide you with an ID and a password. If you can please send these to us and leave the TeamViewer software open.**_
7. _**To reload the sign in software double tap the 'InVentry Core' icon on the desktop**_

We will be waiting for your response.

Kind regards,

Sachin Gupta

Sign up by 28 June for online work experience

Dear Catherine,

Barclays LifeSkills
<https://click.emails.barclays.co.uk/?qs=f68c40ad0a8e9a3ed73cdf2edbc9c997c70d3abccdb04a8603f4a0c8bb2a29e3d2b1abc8488381ca4668690d6fc8024800d998123a8e1e23259a5329ec781c32>
has the tools and resources to help support you and your students in
developing the skills they need for their future careers.

Next month, our incredibly popular *online work experience programme*
returns, which starts on *1 July.* This is the perfect opportunity for
students to gain insight into a range of job roles and understand what
skills are used within a bank. The programme is not limited to those
thinking about a career in financial services as the knowledge and skills
students will learn can be transferred to other industries. Students will
have until *28 June* to sign up.

In addition to the online work experience programme, we have a range of
curriculum-linked resources you can work through with your students to
support them to enter the world of work with confidence. Below, you will
find tools like our CV Builder, which your students can use to develop a
strong CV, or the Virtual Work Experience tool, which allows them to build
upon their workplace skills.

Login today to access all our resources.
Login
<https://click.emails.barclays.co.uk/?qs=f68c40ad0a8e9a3e99b29fcbb956f42e851acfdffb4bcaf5875e5f73b9055f04a27c94d488f5c22fc1eeb2253048fc46245f26745ffb2718e99aeefdfcbfa875>

Online work experience programme
<https://click.emails.barclays.co.uk/?qs=f68c40ad0a8e9a3e7be478e0b4a6ea844e122dafab704f3a7e05a4de4e78b8e734876ceeddaa72ba9198229e6599281e50094092d3329fd481d23687ab8182e9>

Help provide your students (14-19) with the knowledge and skills they need
to develop career aspirations with the Barclays LifeSkills online work
experience programme *starting on Monday, 1 July.* They will gain insight
into what it is like working at a bank, have the chance to hear from
Barclays employees, and build core transferable skills they can take into
any career or industry. The programme takes place after school and includes
five live webinars, activities to test and deepen their learning, and the
opportunity to complete a project.

The *deadline to register is 28 June.* The programme is free to join, but
students will need their own technology to take part.
Find out more
<https://click.emails.barclays.co.uk/?qs=f68c40ad0a8e9a3e7be478e0b4a6ea844e122dafab704f3a7e05a4de4e78b8e734876ceeddaa72ba9198229e6599281e50094092d3329fd481d23687ab8182e9>

CV Builder
Use our free CV builder tool with your students (14-19) to help them build
their own CVs from scratch. They will learn how to tailor their CV to
showcase the skills and experience they have that is relevant to a specific
role and employer, to help them stand out from others. Once they’ve
finished, they can then download their CV as a Word document.
Go to tool >
<https://click.emails.barclays.co.uk/?qs=f68c40ad0a8e9a3e90f9631f4f92b9dc5ec26b820652f1004a62414d3a29b1f687397d94c0b4c53e661f0d0956cd9da8b5e4bb7976ad6525c1b5b6bdc4f4dc10>
[image: Virtual Work Experience Tool]

Virtual Work Experience tool
If you’re looking for other ways to get your students to engage with
workplace skills, our Virtual Work Experience tool is a great place to
start. It takes 20 minutes to complete, with an interactive video element
allowing students to learn about the different departments of a company,
where they will meet various people and help them to solve problems and
complete tasks.
Go to tool >
<https://click.emails.barclays.co.uk/?qs=f68c40ad0a8e9a3e8e924614116d8998d904aa50a91750277e591a7f845d4202f4e41d69ed6864ff44c5cf45a14e8fe6ae548d53bbc8791e79ca4854ae98cbf7>

Social action toolkit
Explore this toolkit with your students (14-19) to get them thinking about
how to get involved in social action, the potential benefits to their
community and possible future employment. It contains ideas and activities
to build a social action programme at your school, with insight from fellow
educators to broaden your own knowledge. There is also advice for students
within the toolkit on how to best showcase their experiences on their CV.
Go to lesson >

From: Helpdesk <helpdesk@schoolicts.co.uk>
Sent: 14 June 2024 09:18
To: C Carr <c.carr@huntington-ed.org.uk>
Subject: Re: Unable to reset password - Ticket Update [ID:2422364]


Hi Claire


Once the patches have been authorised to the school's Solus I will let you know.  Below are the instructions for your IT.



Patches 19098 and 20249. These will grant execute permissions to all SIMS objects. As these Patches are a database install procedure and will grant execute permissions to all SIMS objects, they must be applied using the SQL System Administrator credentials when all users are logged out of SIMS.net.


Patch 19098 will need to be applied first, and Patch 20249 will need to be applied second. Extract the zip files and apply the Patches against the SIMS database. With all Patches, it is important to apply these at a quiet time and once a backup has been taken of the SIMS database.

If the Patches do not resolve the issue, then you will need to reattach the SIMS database. Log into dBattach and detach the SIMS database.
Cut the SIMS MDF and SIMS LDF out of the SQL DATA folder (e.g. C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL12.MSSQLSERVER\MSSQL\DATA) to the server desktop.
Log back into dBattach and attach the cut SIMS MDF.

Please reply to this e-mail to respond.


Thank you.

Digital - Microsoft 365
Office 365 A1 Plus for education will retire on August 1 2024

Office 365 A1 Plus is being retired by Microsoft to ensure schools have
compliant licensing plans, and to support the transition to cloud licences
Microsoft 365 A3 and Microsoft 365 A5. Microsoft Office 365 A1 Plus program
is an Office subscription that includes Office desktop apps for qualified
schools that purchased Office institution-wide for faculty and staff.

Previously any school who purchased an Open Value Subscription Education
Solutions (OVS-ES) annual volume licence agreement would get the Office 365
A1 Plus licence added to their Microsoft 365 Tenancy. Find out more here.
<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208501?source=newsletter&guid=04710F04-380B-4CBB-BFA0-2D6C2D6D7DEE>

If you have a Software and Infrastructure contract with NYES Digital, no
further action is required. The support team will check the licences for
you.

What happens if you don’t have the above contract?

Then…
If you’d like to check yourself, you can do this from the Microsoft 365
Admin Portal.

   1. Navigate to the M365 Admin Portal https://admin.microsoft.com
   <https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208502?source=newsletter&guid=04710F04-380B-4CBB-BFA0-2D6C2D6D7DEE>
-
   Login as your school's Microsoft 365 Administrator.
   2. On the left-hand navigation menu, go to Billing > Licenses.
   3. Look for Office 365 A1 Plus for Faculty and Office 365 A1 Plus for
   Student assigned licenses.

You will be currently using one of the following:

*Office 365 A1*
Free online Office productivity and learning tools. Includes online web
versions of Word, Excel, PowerPoint, OneNote, Microsoft Teams, and
additional classroom tools.
*Office 365 A1 Plus *
Offers everything that comes with Office 365 A1 and also includes the full
desktop apps for Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) not
just the online web versions.

*After all existing Office 365 A1 Plus licences expire on August 1st, 2024,
schools will have the choice to:*

1. If the school has an active Microsoft OVS-ES volume licence agreement,
which includes the Desktop apps:

   1. Anyone with an A1 Plus licence after August 1st will need to be moved
   to an Office 365 A1 licence, the Office 365 A1 licences are free to schools.
   2. Request Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise licences added to the
   school Tenancy. This will add licences for the full Office Desktop apps.
   3. Assign M365 Apps for Enterprise to staff and students who require
   licences for the full desktop Office applications.

2. If the school does not have a valid OVS-ES agreement, the school can
purchase Microsoft 365 Education Cloud Solution Provided (CSP) A3 and A5
licences.


Do you have an Software and Infrastructure Service Level Agreement with
NYES Digital?

*Yes and have an active OVS-ES:*

   - NYES Digital will move all your Office 365 A1 Plus licensed users to
   Office 365 A1
   - NYES Digital will add the Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise to your
   Microsoft 365 Tenancy
   - NYES Digital will assign the Microsoft 365 Apps to the schools users
   who previously had A1 Plus licences.

*Yes but do not have an active OVS-ES agreement:*

   - NYES Digital will move all your Office A1 Plus licensed users to
   Office A1
   - NYES Digital will provide a quote for Microsoft 365 A3 licences for
   your Faculty and Students.

Customers with a Software and Infrastructure Service level Agreement with
NYES Digital will not need to do anything. NYES Digital will move your
licenses for you and if you have volume license OVS-ES agreement we will
ensure that your staff are provided with the Microsoft 365 Apps.

*No, you are not yet a customer of NYES Digital *
Please contact - nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/211053?source=newsletter&guid=04710F04-380B-4CBB-BFA0-2D6C2D6D7DEE>
and request a quote to manage your Microsoft 365 Tenancy, we will also be
able to provide you with Microsoft 365 A3 licences.

Should you have any questions or want to know more about the transition
process, please do not hesitate to contact our NYES Digital support team.

Email: nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
Phone: 01609 536086
NYES Operates UK Wide.

[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=4e9d15b4-050f-48dc-be2a-3504430b28c4&size=Size600]
Digital - Microsoft 365
Office 365 A1 Plus for education will retire on August 1 2024


Office 365 A1 Plus is being retired by Microsoft to ensure schools have compliant licensing plans, and to support the transition to cloud licences Microsoft 365 A3 and Microsoft 365 A5. Microsoft Office 365 A1 Plus program is an Office subscription that includes Office desktop apps for qualified schools that purchased Office institution-wide for faculty and staff.

Previously any school who purchased an Open Value Subscription Education Solutions (OVS-ES) annual volume licence agreement would get the Office 365 A1 Plus licence added to their Microsoft 365 Tenancy. Find out more here.<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208501?source=newsletter&guid=4C2718BB-203E-4EBA-8ED7-6D6CA8344E5E>



[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=de129d56-b683-4b16-8a8e-773986f6d5fb&size=Size600]


If you have a Software and Infrastructure contract with NYES Digital, no further action is required. The support team will check the licences for you.

What happens if you don’t have the above contract?

Then…
If you’d like to check yourself, you can do this from the Microsoft 365 Admin Portal.

  1.  Navigate to the M365 Admin Portal https://admin.microsoft.com<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208502?source=newsletter&guid=4C2718BB-203E-4EBA-8ED7-6D6CA8344E5E> - Login as your school's Microsoft 365 Administrator.
  2.  On the left-hand navigation menu, go to Billing > Licenses.
  3.  Look for Office 365 A1 Plus for Faculty and Office 365 A1 Plus for Student assigned licenses.



[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=8a96af59-9bf5-4e4b-87fb-032d4111c8f3&size=Size600]

[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=64fcd010-3df9-4722-80a9-f0daf4916457&size=Size600]


You will be currently using one of the following:

Office 365 A1
Free online Office productivity and learning tools. Includes online web versions of Word, Excel, PowerPoint, OneNote, Microsoft Teams, and additional classroom tools.
Office 365 A1 Plus
Offers everything that comes with Office 365 A1 and also includes the full desktop apps for Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) not just the online web versions.

After all existing Office 365 A1 Plus licences expire on August 1st, 2024, schools will have the choice to:

1. If the school has an active Microsoft OVS-ES volume licence agreement, which includes the Desktop apps:

  1.  Anyone with an A1 Plus licence after August 1st will need to be moved to an Office 365 A1 licence, the Office 365 A1 licences are free to schools.
  2.  Request Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise licences added to the school Tenancy. This will add licences for the full Office Desktop apps.
  3.  Assign M365 Apps for Enterprise to staff and students who require licences for the full desktop Office applications.

2. If the school does not have a valid OVS-ES agreement, the school can purchase Microsoft 365 Education Cloud Solution Provided (CSP) A3 and A5 licences.




[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=94513c8f-8f03-4bca-bb6c-ddfbe3f81ab4&size=Size600]


Do you have an Software and Infrastructure Service Level Agreement with NYES Digital?

Yes and have an active OVS-ES:

  *   NYES Digital will move all your Office 365 A1 Plus licensed users to Office 365 A1
  *   NYES Digital will add the Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise to your Microsoft 365 Tenancy
  *   NYES Digital will assign the Microsoft 365 Apps to the schools users who previously had A1 Plus licences.

Yes but do not have an active OVS-ES agreement:

  *   NYES Digital will move all your Office A1 Plus licensed users to Office A1
  *   NYES Digital will provide a quote for Microsoft 365 A3 licences for your Faculty and Students.

Customers with a Software and Infrastructure Service level Agreement with NYES Digital will not need to do anything. NYES Digital will move your licenses for you and if you have volume license OVS-ES agreement we will ensure that your staff are provided with the Microsoft 365 Apps.

No, you are not yet a customer of NYES Digital
Please contact - nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/211053?source=newsletter&guid=4C2718BB-203E-4EBA-8ED7-6D6CA8344E5E> and request a quote to manage your Microsoft 365 Tenancy, we will also be able to provide you with Microsoft 365 A3 licences.



[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=0F99DF47-DFEF-45E7-A049-2E59AF4220AA&size=Size600]


Should you have any questions or want to know more about the transition process, please do not hesitate to contact our NYES Digital support team.

Email: nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
Phone: 01609 536086

Digital - Microsoft 365
Office 365 A1 Plus for education will retire on August 1 2024

Office 365 A1 Plus is being retired by Microsoft to ensure schools have compliant licensing plans, and to support the transition to cloud licences Microsoft 365 A3 and Microsoft 365 A5. Microsoft Office 365 A1 Plus program is an Office subscription that includes Office desktop apps for qualified schools that purchased Office institution-wide for faculty and staff.

Previously any school who purchased an Open Value Subscription Education Solutions (OVS-ES) annual volume licence agreement would get the Office 365 A1 Plus licence added to their Microsoft 365 Tenancy. Find out more here.<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208501?source=newsletter&guid=A99C8EB2-9D25-4923-B122-9120623A47B6>

[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=de129d56-b683-4b16-8a8e-773986f6d5fb&size=Size600]

If you have a Software and Infrastructure contract with NYES Digital, no further action is required. The support team will check the licences for you.

What happens if you don’t have the above contract?

Then…
If you’d like to check yourself, you can do this from the Microsoft 365 Admin Portal.

  1.  Navigate to the M365 Admin Portal https://admin.microsoft.com<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/208502?source=newsletter&guid=A99C8EB2-9D25-4923-B122-9120623A47B6> - Login as your school's Microsoft 365 Administrator.
  2.  On the left-hand navigation menu, go to Billing > Licenses.
  3.  Look for Office 365 A1 Plus for Faculty and Office 365 A1 Plus for Student assigned licenses.

[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=8a96af59-9bf5-4e4b-87fb-032d4111c8f3&size=Size600]
[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=64fcd010-3df9-4722-80a9-f0daf4916457&size=Size600]

You will be currently using one of the following:

Office 365 A1
Free online Office productivity and learning tools. Includes online web versions of Word, Excel, PowerPoint, OneNote, Microsoft Teams, and additional classroom tools.
Office 365 A1 Plus
Offers everything that comes with Office 365 A1 and also includes the full desktop apps for Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook) not just the online web versions.

After all existing Office 365 A1 Plus licences expire on August 1st, 2024, schools will have the choice to:

1. If the school has an active Microsoft OVS-ES volume licence agreement, which includes the Desktop apps:

  1.  Anyone with an A1 Plus licence after August 1st will need to be moved to an Office 365 A1 licence, the Office 365 A1 licences are free to schools.
  2.  Request Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise licences added to the school Tenancy. This will add licences for the full Office Desktop apps.
  3.  Assign M365 Apps for Enterprise to staff and students who require licences for the full desktop Office applications.

2. If the school does not have a valid OVS-ES agreement, the school can purchase Microsoft 365 Education Cloud Solution Provided (CSP) A3 and A5 licences.


[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=94513c8f-8f03-4bca-bb6c-ddfbe3f81ab4&size=Size600]

Do you have an Software and Infrastructure Service Level Agreement with NYES Digital?

Yes and have an active OVS-ES:

  *   NYES Digital will move all your Office 365 A1 Plus licensed users to Office 365 A1
  *   NYES Digital will add the Microsoft 365 Apps for Enterprise to your Microsoft 365 Tenancy
  *   NYES Digital will assign the Microsoft 365 Apps to the schools users who previously had A1 Plus licences.

Yes but do not have an active OVS-ES agreement:

  *   NYES Digital will move all your Office A1 Plus licensed users to Office A1
  *   NYES Digital will provide a quote for Microsoft 365 A3 licences for your Faculty and Students.

Customers with a Software and Infrastructure Service level Agreement with NYES Digital will not need to do anything. NYES Digital will move your licenses for you and if you have volume license OVS-ES agreement we will ensure that your staff are provided with the Microsoft 365 Apps.

No, you are not yet a customer of NYES Digital
Please contact - nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk<https://nyes.info/Newsletter/ExternalLink/211053?source=newsletter&guid=A99C8EB2-9D25-4923-B122-9120623A47B6> and request a quote to manage your Microsoft 365 Tenancy, we will also be able to provide you with Microsoft 365 A3 licences.

[https://images.sla-portals.co.uk//https://nyes.info/File/NewsletterIssueImage/?imageGuid=0F99DF47-DFEF-45E7-A049-2E59AF4220AA&size=Size600]

Should you have any questions or want to know more about the transition process, please do not hesitate to contact our NYES Digital support team.

Email: nyes.digital@northyorks.gov.uk
Phone: 01609 536086

NYES Operates UK Wide.

[required] Title: Sims Next Gen Preparation - Ticket Update [ID:2417961]
Description:
Good Afternoon



To ensure all schools are Next Gen ready, ESS have mandated that the following must be applied as soon as possible. 

 Please ensure the following has been applied or updated:

– SIMS Spring Release 2024 (7.216) 

– DEX Patch 28258


– Webview2 Installed and running https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/webview2/?form=MA13LH <https://developer.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/webview2/?form=MA13LH>


- SIMS Services Manager (SSM) version 1.4.8.0 and set to Auto Run/Auto update

– Run Dex config wizard which can be accessed via Tools/Setups/Dex Configuration. You will need a Sims ID login with multi site access for this part. 
Please give us a call or drop us an email when all the other parts are complete and we can login remotely with you to do this. 

After the Dex Config has been run, information should show in the sims data exchange services box in SSM (The SIMS Data Exchange Service package version should be no less than 1.0.8809.18002


If you need any assistance or have any questions regarding this please reply to this email or give us a call on 0345 2226802




Please reply to this e-mail to respond.


Thank you.

> Dear Vanessa Keel,
>
> Please provide the following article to your IT team, should they need
> assistance please ask them to provide direct dials.
>
>
>
> This should however be all they need. Take care
>
>
> How to install SIMS products on a new workstation via SOLUS 3
> KB0052384
> Introduction
>
> The following article will take you through the process of installing SIMS
> on a new workstation using SOLUS 3.
>
> This article assumes that SOLUS 3 has already been installed and
> configured on the server.
>
> The steps to install SIMS can also be applied to installing FMS and
> Discover.
>
> If a SOLUS 3 agent has already been installed on the workstation, but you
> are having issues with the agent and wish to reinstall it, it is highly
> recommended to instead follow the steps in the KB article below.
>
> KB0044360 - SOLUS 3 - How to perform a clean uninstallation /
> reinstallation of the SOLUS 3 Agent
> <https://customer.support-ess.com/csm?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0044360>
>
>
> If installing SIMS on the workstation for the first time, please continue
> with the steps below to add the new workstation in to the SOLUS 3
> environment.
> Instructions
>
> 1) On the server, open *SOLUS 3 Deployment Server UI *using the shortcut
> on the *Desktop*
>
> 2) Navigate to *Environment | Targets | Clients*
>
> 3) Click the *Add* button
>
> 4) Place a *tick* in to the products that you wish to have installed e.g.
> *SIMS*, *SIMS Discover*, *FMS*
>
> 5) Click the *Choose Clients* button
>
> 6) Locate the new workstation on your *Network*. You can also locate the
> workstation by browsing your domain's Active Directory by selecting the
> *AD* radio button. Alternatively, if you know the workstation's hostname
> or IP address, this can be entered in to the field at the bottom and SOLUS
> 3 will attempt to detect it.
>
> 7) Click the arrow to move the workstation over to the *SELECTED
> COMPUTERS* section and click *OK*
>
> 8) You will be prompted to enter the *Domain\Administrator* credentials.
>
> 9) Click *Save*
>
> 10) SOLUS 3 will now attempt to install an Agent on to the new
> workstation. The status of this can be viewed within *Environment |
> Agents | Agents*
>
>
>
> 11) Once the installation of the Agent has finished, the selected product
> will then automatically begin to download and install on to the desired
> workstation.
>
> 12) Staff who are currently using the workstation will notice the
> following popup from the SOLUS 3 Agent  in the Windows system tray.
>
> 13) Staff can hasten the deployment of SIMS by clicking the *Deploy Now* button
> which will skip the 2 minute timer.
>
>
>
> 14) The desired product (be it SIMS, FMS or Discover) will then begin to
> install on to the workstation.
>
> 15) When the deployment has finished, you will see the following message
> in the *SOLUS 3 Agent Notifier* window and the user can now launch the
> software via the Windows *START* menu and log in.
>
>
>
>
>
>
>

---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: WJEC E-Assessment Team (WJEC CBAC) <e-assessment@wjec.co.uk>
Date: Mon, 3 Jun 2024 at 15:05
Subject: Important information regarding Level 1/2 Construction and the
Built Environment Unit 1 (E819) on-screen examination
To: WJEC E-Assessment Team (WJEC CBAC) <e-assessment@wjec.co.uk>




Dear Colleagues,

Keycodes are now available for the following on-screen exam: *Level 1/2
Construction and the Built Environment Unit 1 (E819)* * – 12/06/2024 - PM*

*Please ensure you do the following*:

*Before the exam day*

Log in to Surpass (*https://wjec.surpass.com <https://wjec.surpass.com/>*). If
you have forgotten your login, click on 'can't access your account' and
enter your username/email address. Follow the instructions in the email
from *noreply@surpass.com <noreply@surpass.com>*.

   - Go to Test Administration and Invigilate.
   - Check that all entered candidates have a keycode showing.
   - Add any authorised extra time for your candidates.
   - Print the Invigilation Pack. Ensure you apply the same level of
   security as you would for live examination papers.
   - Please read our e-Assessment Guides on the home page of Surpass as
   they take you through each stage of running our on-screen examinations.
   - Surpass will only allow one login per user. If you need additional
   Surpass user accounts please email *e-assessment@wjec.co.uk
   <e-assessment@wjec.co.uk>* with details of those who need accounts.

*During the exam*

   - Candidates: launch the WJEC SecureClient software, and enter the
   keycode and PIN when prompted.
   - Centre invigilators: log in to Surpass (Test
   Administration>Invigilate).
      - Exams can be paused and resumed here.
         - Absent/Withdrawn candidates – void their keycode.
         - Present candidates – ensure that a green tick is showing at the
         end of the exam. Please contact us if any other symbol is
showing at the
         end.

*Following the exam*

   - Complete the attendance register and return to *e-assessment@wjec.co.uk
   <e-assessment@wjec.co.uk>*.

*Software (please send this to the IT Support at your centre)*

   - Please check your version of the WJEC SecureClient by launching
   SecureClient and click "Surpass, powering assessment". The current version
   is *12.34.076.052 (updated 1st March 2024) *with the icon being a blue
   WJEC logo. If you installed SecureClient before October 2023, you
   will need to uninstall and reinstall.
   - The latest version of SecureClient can be found here:
*https://wjec.surpass.com/LaunchTest/SecureDelivery
   <https://wjec.surpass.com/LaunchTest/SecureDeliveryf>* and please follow
   the *Installing SecureClient guide
   <http://web.download.wjec.co.uk/surpass/Surpass_HomePage/Installation%20Guide.pdf>*
on
   the Home tab of Surpass.
   - If you have not completed a mock exam or a system check test since
   *01/03/2024* you will need to schedule and complete a test using
   candidate level access. For guidance regarding this, please follow
the *Centre
   Staff User Guide
   <http://web.download.wjec.co.uk/surpass/Surpass_HomePage/Centre%20Staff%20User%20Guide.pdf>*
   .

If you have difficulty with any of the above then please contact us
immediately.

Regards

e-Assessment Team / Tîm e-Asesu

029 2026 5328

*e-assessment@wjec.co.uk <e-assessment@wjec.co.uk>*

Hi Oliver

Thank you for contacting Quadient

Please see the below instructions to get your new machine up and running

If you can please consult your IT department and inform them that an IP
configuration checker was completed and displayed the following results

Media State - Conn
IP add status - DHCP
Ping Gateway - *FAILED*
DNS 1 - Succeeded
DNS 2 - Succeeded
Ping Proxy - *FAILED*
Spine Add Res - Succeeded
Ping Spine with Proxy - *FAILED*
Ping Spine No Proxy - Succeeded

These results indicate that the proxy server config settings entered does
not match the config settings in place on your network and the reserved IP
address may not match the network IP range, if you could please double
check the settings and follow the steps below

Menu > Supervisor > 07610 > Communication > LAN settings > DHCP AUTO > DNS
AUTO > Enter both DNS addresses > OK > Take note of the Machine MAC Address
> OK > Select proxy option (if using a proxy, select ON please enter proxy
url/port/domain name and password) > OK > You'll be taken back to the
Communication settings Menu

Please note: If you are planning on assigning a static IP address, change
DHCP/DNS AUTO to MANUAL
If you are no longer using proxy then please select off and then proceed
with the following.

*Firewall settings*

- Ensure a *“new rule”* is created to allow for both inbound and out bound
traffic on Port 443
- Make sure there is an exception on your firewall for access to
*uk-meterservices.neopost.com
<http://uk-meterservices.neopost.com>*

Switch the machine OFF via the mains
Remove the LAN cable
Switch the machine ON without the LAN cable plugged
OK any errors you see until you get to the Home screen
Reconnect the LAN cable
Press the Coins button
Select Audit
OK, this should then connect and transact and return successful.

If you require any further assistance, please don't hesitate to call us on
0845 880 0000 option 1 and option 2 for Helpdesk and Quote Ref : 02427251


Kind Regards
Mustafa

>
>
> How to install SIMS products on a new workstation via SOLUS 3
> KB0052384
> Introduction
>
> The following article will take you through the process of installing SIMS
> on a new workstation using SOLUS 3.
>
> This article assumes that SOLUS 3 has already been installed and
> configured on the server.
>
> The steps to install SIMS can also be applied to installing FMS and
> Discover.
>
> If a SOLUS 3 agent has already been installed on the workstation, but you
> are having issues with the agent and wish to reinstall it, it is highly
> recommended to instead follow the steps in the KB article below.
>
> KB0044360 - SOLUS 3 - How to perform a clean uninstallation /
> reinstallation of the SOLUS 3 Agent
> <https://customer.support-ess.com/csm?id=kb_article_view&sysparm_article=KB0044360>
>
>
> If installing SIMS on the workstation for the first time, please continue
> with the steps below to add the new workstation in to the SOLUS 3
> environment.
> Instructions
>
> 1) On the server, open *SOLUS 3 Deployment Server UI *using the shortcut
> on the *Desktop*
>
> 2) Navigate to *Environment | Targets | Clients*
>
> 3) Click the *Add* button
>
> 4) Place a *tick* in to the products that you wish to have installed e.g.
> *SIMS*, *SIMS Discover*, *FMS*
>
> 5) Click the *Choose Clients* button
>
> 6) Locate the new workstation on your *Network*. You can also locate the
> workstation by browsing your domain's Active Directory by selecting the
> *AD* radio button. Alternatively, if you know the workstation's hostname
> or IP address, this can be entered in to the field at the bottom and SOLUS
> 3 will attempt to detect it.
>
> 7) Click the arrow to move the workstation over to the *SELECTED
> COMPUTERS* section and click *OK*
>
> 8) You will be prompted to enter the *Domain\Administrator* credentials.
>
> 9) Click *Save*
>
> 10) SOLUS 3 will now attempt to install an Agent on to the new
> workstation. The status of this can be viewed within *Environment |
> Agents | Agents*
>
>
>
> 11) Once the installation of the Agent has finished, the selected product
> will then automatically begin to download and install on to the desired
> workstation.
>
> 12) Staff who are currently using the workstation will notice the
> following popup from the SOLUS 3 Agent  in the Windows system tray.
>
> 13) Staff can hasten the deployment of SIMS by clicking the *Deploy Now* button
> which will skip the 2 minute timer.
>
>
>
> 14) The desired product (be it SIMS, FMS or Discover) will then begin to
> install on to the workstation.
>
> 15) When the deployment has finished, you will see the following message
> in the *SOLUS 3 Agent Notifier* window and the user can now launch the
> software via the Windows *START* menu and log in.
>
>
>
>
